## Convergence Conditions

The loop exits when ANY of these occur:

1. **No Valid Revisions**: All lines aligned or below threshold
2. **Max Iterations Reached**: Safety limit (default 10)
3. **No Borders Found**: Block has no right borders to align

### Typical Convergence

Most diagrams converge in 1-2 iterations:

```
Iteration 1: Find target, generate N revisions, apply all
Iteration 2: Re-analyze, all aligned, 0 revisions, converge
```

### Pathological Cases

Some inputs may not converge naturally:

```
# Conflicting borders at different columns:
| A |
| B   |
| C     |
```

With max_iters=10, we apply 10 rounds of padding then stop.

## Revision Application

```rust
fn apply_revision(lines: &mut [String], revision: &Revision) {
    match revision {
        Revision::PadBeforeSuffixBorder { line_idx, spaces_to_add, .. } => {
            let line = &lines[*line_idx];
            let trimmed = line.trim_end();
            let prefix = &trimmed[..trimmed.len() - 1]; // All but last char
            let last_char = trimmed.chars().last().unwrap();
            lines[*line_idx] = format!(
                "{}{}{}\n",
                prefix,
                " ".repeat(*spaces_to_add),
                last_char
            );
        }
        Revision::AddSuffixBorder { line_idx, border_char, target_column } => {
            let line = &lines[*line_idx];
            let trimmed = line.trim_end();
            let current_width = visual_width(trimmed);
            let padding = target_column.saturating_sub(current_width);
            lines[*line_idx] = format!(
                "{}{}{}\n",
                trimmed,
                " ".repeat(padding),
                border_char
            );
        }
    }
}
```

